@node "FREEWARE" "FREEware"

 I am releasing these objects as freeware because this is my way of giving back to all the other Amiga user that have written some really cool programs.


 tHE ARCHIVE CAN BE FREELY DISTRIBUTED AS LONG AS ALL FILES REMAIN INTACT. IF YOU WANT TO CONVERT THEM INTO ANOTHER FORMAT, YOU MAY REPLACE THE OBJECTS, BUT KEEP THIS GUIDE FILE AND ADD ANY INFORMATION NEEDED TO IT.  (IF YOU NEED AN OTHER FORMAT @{"E-MAIL ME" link "author" 0} AND I WILL RUN THEM THROUGH PIXEL PRO AND SEND THEM TO YOU). IF YOU INCLUDE IT ON A CD (EXCEPT THE AMINET) YOU MUST SEND ME A COPY OF THE CD.
@endnode

@node "Station5" "Space Station 5"

 Space Station.ibj

 The space station from 2001

 Scale: 1 imagine unit = 1 meter

 Key the Global fx "Haze" to r=222, G=222, B=255. This the the color of the windows and will give them a nice glow.  I looks good but I didn't have great refences to work from so the finer details are very simple.

 The @{b}Space station.fak@{ub} is a small stand-in model to use in the stage editor (because it loads faster and redraws faster).  Build the scene using the fake then go to the action editor and replace the fak with the object.




 @{u}TEXTURES@{uu}:
   -Dirt               Standard Imagine Texture
   -Cylindhullplate    Essence II texture
   -RdDthStr           Standard Imagine Texture
   -DethStar           Standard Imagine Texture
@endnode

